{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_36", "type": "agent_message", "text": "T816 is now `in_review`. I delivered a sanitized Sprint 6 Phase 1 live-data fixture pack that removes the implausible thresholds Ivan flagged, and I kept the old Sprint 4 artifact untouched by writing the new pack to Sprint 6-specific paths.\n\nKey artifacts are [filtered_markets_live_fixture.json](/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/grace/filtered_markets_live_fixture.json), [live_phase1_fixture.json](/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/grace/live_phase1_fixture.json), [live_phase1_expected.json](/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/grace/live_phase1_expected.json), and [live_phase1_validation_report.md](/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/grace/live_phase1_validation_report.md). I also refactored [market_filter.js](/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/grace/market_filter.js) to normalize live-shaped payloads through Bob\u2019s shared normalizer and surface rejected-invalid markets explicitly.\n\nVerification passed with `node /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/grace/verify_live_phase1_fixture.js`: 11 fixture cases, 9 valid normalized markets, 4 qualifying, 2 middle-range excludes, 2 extreme-ratio manual reviews, and 2 rejected-invalid payloads. I DM\u2019d Alice, Ivan, and Olivia and posted the handoff to team channel; the task is waiting on review approval."}}
